name: Zucchini and Soy Bean Stir Fry
author: Kierston
summary: I invented this while goofing around in the kitchen. It ended up being a hit with my family! If the veggies are steamed tender-crisp before being thrown in the pan, it cuts the cooking time in half and makes it a quick healthy lunch! Serve warm, topped with toasted sesame seeds.
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower, edamame, carrots, and water in a microwave-safe bowl
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave for 1 minute until vegetables are tender
Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat; add onion
Cook and stir until onion is softened and beginning to brown, about 10 minutes
Stir cooked broccoli, cauliflower, edamame, carrots, zucchini, mushrooms, and garlic into the pan; cook and stir until vegetables are cooked through, about 5 minutes
Stir in reduced-sodium teriyaki sauce and agave nectar; cook 5 more minutes
